{
  "texts": [
    "We see a distinction for the types of code editors experienced by different personas.",
    "Authoring with low-level visualization libraries (e.g., Gosling [40]) often had a steep learning curve and was sometimes found to be impossible after initial attempts for \"Bioinformaticians\" and some \"Computational Biologists\" (P5, P9, P8, P6, P13, P19).",
    "They found this unfortunate because they saw potential in libraries, such as Gosling [40], to produce \"desirable\" or \"pleasant visualizations\".",
    "\"It's doing nice visualizations, but it took me some time to grasp.\"",
    "\"It's beautiful."
  ]
}